title: For Sale:  1945 Enfield Jungle Carbine NO5 MK1 ROF (F) 303
location: South Bay L.A., Los Angeles, California
postcontent:
Enfield NO5 Mk1 Jungle Carbine, ROF (F), Royal Ordnance Factory Fazakerley, dated May 1945, chambered in the 303 British round.
This rifle has been there, done that and shows use and wear, but is in good, solid overall shape. 

The receiver and bolt numbers match.  The stock and mag #s are indistinct due to wear, I can't make them out.  I want to remove the handguard tomorrow to photo and confirm barrel number and fluted knox form.  

Serial number M3305.  No.5 Jungle Carbines only have 4 numbers from what I've learned.
The Fazakerley jungle carbines ran from FE1 to FE1000 initial production, then with no letter prefix, followed by A1 to A9999 through Z9999, as cited on enfieldcollector dot com serial numbers page.

The carbine has an 800 yard rear flip up sight.  There's plenty of clearance under this rear sight, you can see plenty of daylight side to side under the sight, which is a result of milling & lightening of the receiver.  

I don't find any import marks, , which would mean it came in to the US before 1968.
if you're local feel free to come over, check it out and prove me wrong.

The barrel band is 8 " in front of the receiver ring (Jungle Carbine copies seem to be around 10 3/4" as on a No. 4 rifle).

For local face-to-face sale only in the Redondo beach and adjacent South Bay L.A. areas (Hawthorne, Manhattan Beach, Torrance ...) If you're local and want to check it out feel free to send an email to set up a meet. All laws apply, FTF FFL PPT in my area only, NOT looking for trades, buyer pays all FFL fees. $400
Thanks for looking.

Includes: FN Herstal Hard Case, Operator's Instructions Manual/paperwork, FNH Pistol Lock, factory test casing, (3) 20 round magazines, and (1) 30 round magazine. PLUS, 1000 rounds RARE FN ammo = 550 rounds SS195LF HOT ammo (11 Boxes of 50 rounds per/box) & 450 rounds RARE SS192 "Green Ammo" (9 Boxes of 50 rounds per/box). **** RARE SS192 “Green Ammo” was produced for ONLY 3 months before FN turned to the SS195LF. The SS192 "Green Ammo" is the predecessor to the current SS195LF which uses the same 27gr HP aluminum core bullet but with a lead free primer, hence the LF designation. The SS192 “green ammo” or environmentally friendly ammo was SS195LF ammo before they changed the name and box. The manufacture (FN Herstal) relates the labeling as a way to visibly mark the packaging so that there is a lower chance for this to be mixed up with SS192 ammunition that contains lead primer. RARE and Highly Collectible!!!
